The paper deals with the problem of fine-grained video attractiveness prediction using multimodal deep learning on a large real-world dataset. The paper involves the use of computer vision techniques for analyzing video content, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques for analyzing user behavior, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques for predicting video attractiveness, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
